as long as my lips are in contact with yours.

290
00:17:37,940 --> 00:17:39,380
I don’t know for now

291
00:17:39,740 --> 00:17:41,340
how I can get it back for good.

292
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:42,380
So,

293
00:17:42,820 --> 00:17:44,820
I’ll hire you for a while

294
00:17:45,180 --> 00:17:46,740
to keep it for me.

295
00:17:47,020 --> 00:17:48,680
Give it back to me temporarily

296
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:50,300
when I need it.

297
00:17:50,380 --> 00:17:51,300
You are crazy!

298
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:53,540
Then tell me,

299
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:57,720
how much I need to pay for this cycle deal?

300
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:00,300
Cycle deal?

301
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:02,460
The term is quite professional.

302
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:04,100
You know what?

303
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:05,600
If you pay me this much,

304
00:18:06,140 --> 00:18:07,380
I’ll work with you!

305
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:11,340
Okay!

306
00:18:12,020 --> 00:18:12,780
It’s a deal!

307
00:18:15,020 --> 00:18:16,880
I’ll draft the contract tonight,

308
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:19,060
and we’ll sign it tomorrow morning.

309
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:20,060
Okay!

310
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:22,620
Whoever bails is a coward!

311
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:31,540
Get on there!

312
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:33,580
Stupid!

313
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,060
Get on!

314
00:18:43,020 --> 00:18:43,780
Come on!

315
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:45,540
Surround, now!

316
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:46,660
Xiao Yongyong!

317
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:49,580
Thank god, you are back!

318
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:52,260
Do you know how much I worried about you?

319
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:55,180
You were taken away by the police today.

320
00:18:55,540 --> 00:18:57,140
The bodyguard leader told me

321
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:59,920
that he can’t hire anybody who has a case record.

322
00:19:00,460 --> 00:19:02,220
He was crazy to say something like that!

323
00:19:02,220 --> 00:19:02,780
So,

324
00:19:02,860 --> 00:19:03,940
I argued with him.

325
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:05,340
If he fired you,

326
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:06,340
I’d quit too!

327
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:07,740
I’ll stay

328
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,160
only if He Buzui stays!

329
00:19:09,660 --> 00:19:11,300
Good for you, buddy!

330
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:12,500
Thank you!

331
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:16,340
But you should stick to this job.

332
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:18,740
To me, it’s an unprofitable tough job.

333
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,400
I wanted to quit long time ago.

334
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:23,260
An unprofitable tough job?

335
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:24,190
What do you mean?

336
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:36,900
I lost!

337
00:19:37,460 --> 00:19:38,380
Stop playing.

338
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:40,310
What did he say about the bonus?

339
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:42,500
Bonus?

340
00:19:43,780 --> 00:19:44,580
I’m afraid

341
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:45,740
it’s none.

342
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:48,660
But he said

343
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:52,380
that he’ll send the salary of this month

344
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:53,430
to your account.

345
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:57,280
That’s thoughtful of him.

346
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:58,500
It’s okay!

347
00:19:58,780 --> 00:19:59,540
You have me!

348
00:19:59,820 --> 00:20:00,820
I’ll support you!

349
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,360
With your poor salary?

350
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:04,880
How’s that gonna help?

351
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:08,100
Then,

352
00:20:10,260 --> 00:20:11,500
let’s sell our blood?

353
00:20:11,780 --> 00:20:12,660
Sell blood?

354
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:14,140
Are you out of your mind?

355
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,580
Crazy!

356
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:15,670
We said the day after tomorrow.

357
00:22:15,860 --> 00:22:18,380
I will pay you off by then.

358
00:22:19,260 --> 00:22:20,060
Open the door!

359
00:22:30,660 --> 00:22:31,540
It’s open.

360
00:22:34,580 --> 00:22:35,510
What do you want?

361
00:22:36,660 --> 00:22:37,460
What are you doing?

362
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:38,520
What are you doing?

363
00:22:38,860 --> 00:22:40,060
Sign the contract!

364
00:22:44,140 --> 00:22:45,980
How did you know I live here?

365
00:22:46,420 --> 00:22:48,020
I saw your address last night

366
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:50,060
when you filled in the form at the police station.

367
00:22:50,060 --> 00:22:51,820
I have photographic memory

368
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:54,840
Take a look.

369
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:56,340
I don’t have so much time.

370
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,700
Are you serious?

371
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:07,790
You live here alone?

372
00:23:09,260 --> 00:23:10,460
My dad went shopping.

373
00:23:12,020 --> 00:23:13,260
Take a look at the contract.

374
00:23:13,260 --> 00:23:14,920
Sign it if you are okay with it.

375
00:23:21,220 --> 00:23:24,340
First party Lu Weixun, second party He buzui.

376
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:26,180
The first party has the right to make adjustment

377
00:23:26,180 --> 00:23:29,140
to the work contents and responsibilities of the second party at any time

378
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:32,540
according to the second party’s abilities and performance.

379
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:34,080
Why didn’t you just put

380
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:36,220
the first party has the right to enslave the second party?

381
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:36,940
I did.

382
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:38,380
On the third page.

383
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:45,540
The first party shall exercise

384
00:23:45,620 --> 00:23:48,460
24-hour working system when necessary.

385
00:23:48,740 --> 00:23:51,540
The second party shall be on call around the clock.

386
00:23:55,540 --> 00:23:56,700
Are you aware of

387
00:23:56,900 --> 00:24:01,140
one thing called labor law?

388
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:01,980
I am.

389
00:24:02,220 --> 00:24:05,420
Payment for working overtime will be counted by the hour.

390
00:24:05,460 --> 00:24:06,700
Double payment

391
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:08,310
for each extra hour.

392
00:24:11,060 --> 00:24:14,380
Then, when can I get my payment?

393
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,340
You’ll be paid in the middle of every month.

394
00:24:16,340 --> 00:24:17,400
6,000 Yuan a month.

395
00:24:18,020 --> 00:24:20,420
6,000 Yuan a month?

396
00:24:21,020 --> 00:24:22,980
Then I’ll be your slave

397
00:24:23,060 --> 00:24:29,340
for 333 months, which is 28 years!

398
00:24:29,460 --> 00:24:30,260
28 years!

399
00:24:30,340 --> 00:24:31,700
Why does it take that long for me to get the money?

400
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:33,820
In 28 years, I’ll be 53 years old.

401
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:34,980
From the medical point of view,

402
00:24:34,980 --> 00:24:37,020
after 53 years old,

403
00:24:37,060 --> 00:24:38,460
the functions of the human body will rapidly decline.

404
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,820
Even if we can still exchange our sense of taste then,

405
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:44,140
it will reduce greatly with the decaying physical condition.

406
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:45,500
An average sense of taste

407
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:46,700
means nothing to me.

408
00:24:46,780 --> 00:24:48,040
I won’t care to have it.

409
00:24:48,140 --> 00:24:49,260
But before that,

410
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:51,260
I have to prepare for the worst!

411
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:53,700
If we can’t exchange our sense of taste for good,

412
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:56,100
I have to make sure that my life and my career

413
00:24:56,140 --> 00:24:58,540
won’t be affected by it!

414
00:24:59,660 --> 00:25:02,980
So my life will become a mess!

415
00:25:03,140 --> 00:25:03,860
Miss He,

416
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:05,380
in my opinion,

417
00:25:05,860 --> 00:25:07,180
I in fact will take bigger risk

418
00:25:07,180 --> 00:25:09,860
hiring you for 28 years.

419
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:11,110
But before that,

420
00:25:11,180 --> 00:25:13,780
as long as we can find a way to exchange our sense of taste for good,

421
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:15,980
we can terminate the contract any time.

422
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:17,760
And I won’t see you ever again!

423
00:25:18,220 --> 00:25:20,150
You can get your money earlier too!

424
00:25:25,140 --> 00:25:26,420
This money…

425
00:25:29,140 --> 00:25:29,860
He Buzui.

426
00:25:30,340 --> 00:25:31,640
Calm!

427
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:33,740
Be calm!

428
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:35,580
You’ve got to have a bottom line!

429
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:38,920
How could you give your dignity up for money?

430
00:25:39,780 --> 00:25:41,620
But if I accept this job,

431
00:25:41,780 --> 00:25:44,540
I can use it to offset the monthly loan.

432
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:48,500
All it takes me is a kiss.

433
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:50,500
I’ll just consider it a dog bite.

434
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:51,140
Of course,

435
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:54,300
it’s not a small amount of money.

436
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,740
If you don’t want to,

437
00:25:57,820 --> 00:25:59,380
I won’t force you…

438
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:04,230
You’ve thought it through?

439
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:05,620
No!

440
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:08,260
No way!

441
00:26:20,420 --> 00:26:21,420
Bro De!

442
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:24,060
What brought you here?

443
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:26,220
Don’t call me that!

444
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:27,700
I’m not your brother!

445
00:26:28,140 --> 00:26:29,540
You are my grandma, okay?

446
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:32,340
The ones who owe money nowadays

447
00:26:32,420 --> 00:26:34,220
are with the real power.

448
00:26:34,420 --> 00:26:36,080
You even shut down your phone.

449
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:38,780
So I’m here to greet you in person!

450
00:26:38,860 --> 00:26:39,580
Bro De!

451
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:40,860
I’m greeting to you!

452
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:42,660
Come on!

453
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:44,460
Please take a seat!

454
00:26:44,580 --> 00:26:45,840
Let me clean it for you.

455
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:47,940
Please!

456
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:51,580
Take a rest!

457
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:53,140
Let me get you some tea!

458
00:26:53,260 --> 00:26:53,860
Okay.

459
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:13,700
Hey, turn around!

460
00:27:14,180 --> 00:27:15,060
Turn around!

461
00:27:19,460 --> 00:27:20,340
Miss He,

462
00:27:21,380 --> 00:27:23,140
you’ll get rich now!

463
00:27:24,140 --> 00:27:26,620
You’ve signed a contract that’ll pay you a large amount of money!

464
00:27:26,620 --> 00:27:28,620
So, about the small money you owe us,

465
00:27:28,700 --> 00:27:29,900
don’t you think…

466
00:27:38,620 --> 00:27:39,420
I understand.

467
00:27:47,020 --> 00:27:48,940
Bro De, let’s talk!

468
00:27:50,140 --> 00:27:52,220
So you won’t pay us, huh?

469
00:27:55,380 --> 00:27:56,510
Bro De, are you okay?

470
00:27:58,700 --> 00:27:59,940
Don’t just stand there!

471
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:02,000
Destroy this place! Don’t look at me!

472
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:03,500
Please! Don’t!

473
00:28:05,620 --> 00:28:06,580
Don’t!

474
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:09,540
Stop!

475
00:28:11,220 --> 00:28:12,820
What you think you are doing?

476
00:28:13,140 --> 00:28:14,260
Hey!

477
00:28:14,420 --> 00:28:15,620
What’s your problem?

478
00:28:16,140 --> 00:28:16,860
Young man,

479
00:28:17,220 --> 00:28:18,480
don’t you know the rule

480
00:28:19,820 --> 00:28:21,700
that debt should be paid?

481
00:28:22,820 --> 00:28:23,860
It’s none of your business!

482
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:24,720
Get out of here!

483
00:28:25,140 --> 00:28:25,700
Go on!

484
00:28:26,020 --> 00:28:27,500
How much does she owe you?

485
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:28,910
What do you mean?

486
00:28:29,180 --> 00:28:29,980
Sounds like

487
00:28:30,060 --> 00:28:31,460
you want to pay it for her?

488
00:28:32,020 --> 00:28:32,900
How much?

489
00:28:35,300 --> 00:28:37,540
It’s a lot of money with interest!

490
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:47,760
I’ll pay it for her.

491
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:52,710
You want to play a hero to save beauty?!

492
00:29:03,180 --> 00:29:05,580
Fight and threat won’t solve any problems.

493
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:07,150
Let’s be practical.

494
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:10,620
Let’s sign a three-party contract.

495
00:29:12,180 --> 00:29:13,780
Why would I use violence

496
00:29:13,860 --> 00:29:15,460
if I can get paid?

497
00:29:24,140 --> 00:29:25,420
Let me be clear.

498
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:27,500
You have to pay every penny!

499
00:29:27,580 --> 00:29:30,660
This is the number showed on the IOU.

500
00:29:31,380 --> 00:29:32,510
You’ll break the law

501
00:29:32,980 --> 00:29:34,380
if you ask more than that.

502
00:29:35,660 --> 00:29:36,590
What do you mean?

503
00:29:36,980 --> 00:29:38,620
This is the total amount I’ll pay back.

504
00:29:38,620 --> 00:29:39,980
It’ll be paid quarterly,

505
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:41,180
and paid off in a year.

506
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:45,140
Are you bargaining with me?

507
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:47,700
Bargaining?

508
00:29:48,380 --> 00:29:50,620
She can’t afford a lawyer, but I can.

509
00:29:51,820 --> 00:29:53,260
Don’t be too greedy!

510
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:55,400
It won’t be good to you!

511
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:57,180
Plus,

512
00:29:57,700 --> 00:30:00,700
you go to her home every month to ask for the money,

513
00:30:01,140 --> 00:30:03,700
even if you destroy her home over and over again,

514
00:30:03,700 --> 00:30:05,020
she still won’t be able to pay you off

515
00:30:05,020 --> 00:30:06,380
in a year.

516
00:30:09,860 --> 00:30:10,660
Alright!

517
00:30:11,340 --> 00:30:11,860
Buddy,

518
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:13,620
you are very straightforward.

519
00:30:13,620 --> 00:30:15,080
Let’s go with your number!

520
00:30:15,780 --> 00:30:16,500
But,

521
00:30:17,020 --> 00:30:18,100
I have one condition.

522
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:19,300
What?

523
00:30:19,420 --> 00:30:21,460
I’ll only pay you quarterly

524
00:30:22,820 --> 00:30:24,350
if she agrees to work for me!

525
00:30:29,940 --> 00:30:32,780
I passed by a planet named after you.

526
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:35,030
Where are you taking me?

527
00:30:36,340 --> 00:30:37,940
Muunas Winery.

528
00:30:38,020 --> 00:30:40,500
Your eyes are clear and shining.

529
00:30:40,660 --> 00:30:43,860
When can you understand my heart?

530
00:30:45,500 --> 00:30:48,180
The day and night on the planet is upside down.

531
00:30:48,340 --> 00:30:51,220
It’s sign for the explosion of love!

532
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:55,860
Run along the trajectory of the universe.

533
00:30:55,980 --> 00:30:58,940
I can find you in my dreams.

534
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:11,340
Mr. Lu.

535
00:31:11,460 --> 00:31:12,060
Mr. Ma.

536
00:31:13,140 --> 00:31:14,070
Long time no see!

537
00:31:16,460 --> 00:31:17,390
Long time no see!

538
00:31:18,900 --> 00:31:20,060
Who’s this lady?

539
00:31:20,620 --> 00:31:21,420
My assistant.

540
00:31:22,700 --> 00:31:23,820
Mr. Ma, nice to meet you.

541
00:31:23,820 --> 00:31:24,880
My name is He Buzui.

542
00:31:25,100 --> 00:31:26,060
He Buzui?

543
00:31:26,780 --> 00:31:27,900
Never get drunk!

544
00:31:28,100 --> 00:31:29,100
Good name!

545
00:31:30,380 --> 00:31:32,140
Cause I can never get drunk!

546
00:31:32,580 --> 00:31:33,980
Have some self-respect!

547
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:36,340
We all live on liquor!

548
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:38,830
Who do you think you are to judge me?

549
00:31:39,540 --> 00:31:41,780
Do you want to take a rest or…

550
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:42,940
We’ll go to the wine cellar now.

551
00:31:42,940 --> 00:31:43,420
Okay.

552
00:31:43,660 --> 00:31:44,660
This way, please.

553
00:31:55,300 --> 00:31:55,780
Here.

554
00:31:59,180 --> 00:32:01,100
It’s so cold in here!

555
00:32:05,300 --> 00:32:07,030
You are not here for a vacation!

556
00:32:07,460 --> 00:32:10,620
This is the temperature most suitable for storing the wine.

557
00:32:10,620 --> 00:32:11,420
Follow us.

558
00:32:13,860 --> 00:32:14,540
Please.

559
00:32:18,380 --> 00:32:19,340
Watch the steps.

560
00:32:28,820 --> 00:32:30,420
This is the product No. 92.

561
00:32:30,620 --> 00:32:31,820
There are 18 barrels.

562
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:33,660
I’ve prepared one glass of sample for each,

563
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:34,720
for you to examine.

564
00:32:35,020 --> 00:32:36,020
Thank you, Mr. Ma.

565
00:32:36,820 --> 00:32:38,900
We’ll take care of the rest.

566
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:39,580
Okay.

567
00:32:39,740 --> 00:32:40,740
I’ll leave now.

568
00:32:57,660 --> 00:32:58,260
Come over.

569
00:33:00,540 --> 00:33:01,540
Why?

570
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:04,100
Exchange the sense of taste.

571
00:33:06,580 --> 00:33:07,820
Now?

572
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:10,660
Here?

573
00:33:10,780 --> 00:33:11,900
Of course!

574
00:33:16,580 --> 00:33:17,700
It’s working time.

575
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:21,060
Please be professional.

576
00:33:37,820 --> 00:33:38,380
Wait!

